d%20of%20Ukraine's%20Unmanned%20Systems%20Forces%2C%20Col.%20Vadym%20Sukharevskyi%2C%20observed%20in%20March%20that%20%26quot%3Bnot%20a%20single%20NATO%20army%20is%20ready%20to%20resist%20the%20cascade%20of%20drones.%26quot%3B%20A%20major%20point%20of%20concern%20has%20been%20the%20Western%20overreliance%20on%20expensive%20missiles%2C%20which%20are%20less%20than%20ideal%20against%20swarms%20of%20cheap%20drones.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2220d5c493-5b65-46d5-88cb-ffbcb0296d01%5C%22%3EA%20new%20arms%20race%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMuch%20of%20Europe%20is%20concerned%20that%20Russia%20could%20launch%20an%20attack%20elsewhere%20on%20the%20continent%2C%20potentially%20sparking%20a%20wider%20war.%20The%20US%2C%20meanwhile%2C%20is%20concerned%20about%20China.%20These%20potential%20conflicts%20wouldn't%20look%20exactly%20like%20the%20war%20against%20Ukraine%E2%80%94%20Western%20militaries%20are%20far%20better%20supplied%20%E2%80%94%20but%20given%20Russia's%20and%20China's%20heavy%20investment%20in%20drone%20tech%2C%20drones%20would%20likely%20play%20a%20central%20role.%20And%20NATO%20knows%20its%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnatos-focus-air-defenses-needed-from-way-russia-fighting-ukraine-2025-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ecurrent%20defenses%20aren't%20ready%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMcCrann%20said%20other%20conflicts%20won't%20look%20like%20Russia's%20war%20against%20Ukraine%2C%20but%20%26quot%3Bwe%20now%20understand%20that%20this%20threat%20is%20here%20to%20stay%20and%20it%20moves%20very%20quickly.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20that%20companies%20working%20on%20a%20solution%20must%20%26quot%3Brealize%20that%20that%20is%20the%20reality%20and%20our%20solutions%20have%20to%20be%20different%20than%20what%20this%20industry%20was%20building%20five%2C%2010%20years%20ago%20when%20we%20first%20started.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMany%20others%20in%20the%20industry%20can%20see%20how%20fast%20things%20are%20changing.%20The%20CEO%20of%20Uk